name: Bukit Timah Nature Reserve
review_text: Good to escape the buzz and buzzle of the city. Used to come here for hike every week but I have since moved house to Thomson. Still one of the best hiking spots.

name: Bukit Timah Nature Reserve
review_text: Very convenient to visit. Can see that they are doing improvements to the commuter facilities there

name: Bukit Timah Nature Reserve
review_text: Nice short and powerful hike with different levels of difficulty. One route is extremely inclined, but you can take other routes with steps to make it easier. With little bit of rain makes the atmosphere very enchanting..

name: Bukit Timah Nature Reserve
review_text: Worth it just for the hike up to the summit. For those who don't know, it's best not to expect a grand view from the top. There is a great view of Singapore quarry from a little off the "main road", though. The trails off the main road are also much more interesting, though they are a bit demanding for average people like me. The best kept secret is the quarry in Hindhede park. For those who can, it's best to go on weekdays if you're looking for quiet...

name: Bukit Timah Nature Reserve
review_text: Love the weather around this time of the year. Even though parking might be a hassle. The walk was a good training before heading out of Singapore for new hikers. Recommend dairy farm loop a few times to build your endurance

name: Bukit Timah Nature Reserve
review_text: My favourite hiking place and I will go there almost every week. Usually crowded on the weekends, but never stop me from going. I will usually walk from my home which is Bukit Panjang then to Bukit Timah Nature Reserve. It is nice to see people from the young and to the old, keeping fit.

name: Bukit Timah Nature Reserve
review_text: Rock path at the moment is closed. Steep slope will welcome you in the beginning. Lots of steps at South view path

name: Bukit Timah Nature Reserve
review_text: Nice place for hiking, if you love nature then this is a good place for in touch with trees, insects, fresh air. The trees seemed very old and big, you smell it and so fragrant. There are several alternatives for hiking route, you can choose the easy, medium and difficult one. The sign provided also very easy ro recognize, the map also easy to read. I will for sure to visit again for different hiking route and be with the nature.

name: Bukit Timah Nature Reserve
review_text: It's the tallest hill in Singapore at 163 metres. There are different routes that have different difficult levels. Families with kids can take the easiest route to get to the peak. To put it simple, it's a great place for hiking and even families outing to sweat it out.

name: Bukit Timah Nature Reserve
review_text: Really nice place for outdoor exercise and being with nature. Singapore is very small and can sometimes feel lacking in outdoor exploration opportunities but this can offer a bit of a reprieve. Quite a few different hiking/walking paths, as well as mountain biking trails. Good place for families to spend the day. It's very popular on weekends and lots of people around. There are some routes that are a bit more challenging in terms of the elevation gain, but anyone with lots of experience outdoors might need to do repeats of routes to really feel a burn. Many opportunities for beginners too.

name: Bukit Timah Nature Reserve
review_text: Nice place for hiking. Just a bit short distance to the hill

name: Bukit Timah Nature Reserve
review_text: Great place to go with the family to get back to nature. Relatively easy hike with a very steep incline in the beginning. But still easy enough for my 6 year old to climb up. The trees will shield you from the sun. Can be crowded. But perfect for a family activity on the weekends.

name: Bukit Timah Nature Reserve
review_text: If you want a quick and effective workout then that's the place. Also there are several trail including cycling trail which leads to other parks like Diary farms and all. It's an amazing experience to go to the summit in the wee hours. It's neither crowded not lonely. Just the right atmosphere.

name: Bukit Timah Nature Reserve
review_text: Bukit Timah Hill is the highest point in Singapore. I love the trails here because of the up slope and down slope, which is ideal for training of our quad muscles for hiking. Train with some weights for resistance and stronger legs. Toilet facilities and water point are available in the park. Don‚Äôt forget to check out Singapore Quarry and Hindhede Quarry when you are there. Many birdie photographers mount their tripods at both the quarries waiting to capture the splendid moments of the different bird species. It is now possible to connect to Bukit Timah Nature Reserve via the Rail Corridor. Nearest MRT station is at Beauty World, and you head to Bukit Anak Road before arriving at the main entrance through Hindhede Drive.

name: Bukit Timah Nature Reserve
review_text: It's real. Steep walk all the way up. But just a short distance so its gonna be fine

name: Bukit Timah Nature Reserve
review_text: LSD run from Bishan to MacRitchie to Bukit Timah and back to Bishan again. Good Sunday weather for a good runüòä

name: Bukit Timah Nature Reserve
review_text: First thing that will come to your mind if you either running or taking a stroll in the wee hours, is the calmness, serene views and beautiful sounds of creatures can be seen and heard. You will be amazed too that this is in the heartland of Singapore. Enjoy the place before someone decided to change the landscape üòå

name: Bukit Timah Nature Reserve
review_text: It has multiple route for different activity and sufficient safety precaution for the hiker

name: Bukit Timah Nature Reserve
review_text: Popular hiking spot from 7am -7pm for old and young weather permitting. Only wish there are some water coolers along the hike to rehydrate. Scenic paths with lots of greeneries providing shade.

name: Bukit Timah Nature Reserve
review_text: Great place to train for mountain hiking trips, with steep slopes and stairs perfect for lugging weighted backpacks up and down. The main road up to the summit is wide, though the smaller side trails from the dairy farm side are narrower and can accommodate one person in each direction. Signboards are frequent and it's unlikely you'll get lost. Bring plenty of water and insect repellent, and stay off the mountain bike trails!

name: Bukit Timah Nature Reserve
review_text: Good for training - there are many routes to go up from! I don't think this is for tourists, for views go to Mcritchie treetop walk!

name: Bukit Timah Nature Reserve
review_text: Good trekking place for beginners.

name: Bukit Timah Nature Reserve
review_text: It has many side routes and map shows clearly where you are stands don't worry about being lost. Many hikers, families, even trail running are here. Nice for 2 hours you can do it all. You will see some lizards or monkey, butterflies, many species of trees. The hike to the top was closed during my time, ask if you don't want to waste your time, but the view over the quarry was nice, partial view.

name: Bukit Timah Nature Reserve
review_text: Great for hiking!!! So refreshing and it relieves stress.

name: Bukit Timah Nature Reserve
review_text: One of the best nature reserves in Singapore, especially for hiking as there are many different types of trails, many entrances and exits and can be decently challenging at points such as the beginning super steep slope (around 50¬∞ or more) or many staircases. It is very safe compared to other nature reserves and there are bicycle trails for those who enjoy cross-country biking (do watch out for the turns though, especially if you like to go high speed).

name: Bukit Timah Nature Reserve
review_text: No travelers, I mean also no. Very nice and peaceful.. rail corridor...

name: Bukit Timah Nature Reserve
review_text: Juz loved visiting this for the trail. Always have something new to discover!

name: Bukit Timah Nature Reserve
review_text: This is a really good place for going hiking for a few hours. Beware though, after 7pm you cannot enter anymore (you can still exit, but you should leave before it gets too dark). Also, we found a swarm of mosquitos all over the ground at one spot, so don't forget to use your safety spray.

name: Bukit Timah Nature Reserve
review_text: Nice place to enjoy the nature.

name: Bukit Timah Nature Reserve
review_text:
Super green jungle in garden city Singapore.
Nice trees, species and other things.
Summit is highest point in Singapore. Must climb to have memorable experience.
Overall I like this park.
Park timing are 7am to 7pm.

name: Bukit Timah Nature Reserve
review_text: Highest natural point in Singapore at about 163 m. Nice rise to trek up on a weekend morning. You can also explore various side trails to walk and feel the nature. Perfect place for mountain bikers. Their trails are different from those of on foot.

name: Bukit Timah Nature Reserve
review_text: Nice little hill at just over 160m and will take 15 mins to get up via the shortest path. The bonus is the difficulty rated Dairy Farm Loop (yellow path) if you fancy a bit more challenge. Set aside one hour for that loop and there will be tons and tons of concrete wet stairs to overcome! üò≥

name: Bukit Timah Nature Reserve
review_text:
Bit too crowded in the morning of public holiday/weekends.

Bring insect repellent, water, portable fan, towel.

Wear a good shoes so you don't roll down the steep slope!

name: Bukit Timah Nature Reserve
review_text: This is a magical place. We went on a Nature Walk on Saturday. Great guide - we learned so much and had fun. There are trails for all different activities. A really special place to go to get away from the City. The Visitor Centre is interesting too. Recommended.

name: Bukit Timah Nature Reserve
review_text: Calming scenic as ever, but I wish it could look less artificial and more natural in the efforts to preserve the soil erosion process. Allow more flowing streams and quarry views. Anyway excellent efforts to the nature preservation  team üëç

name: Bukit Timah Nature Reserve
review_text: So many unexpected trails to explore. Walkways devotedly set up by N Parks - thank you! Plenty of birdlife and there are wild boar, monitor lizards to make you jump in the quiet jungle. A great way to spend a few hours in the greenery. And it's free!

name: Bukit Timah Nature Reserve
review_text: I like to be there in the morning before 8am. Smaller crowd, cool weather and nice sunlight which isn't too overbearing. The long flight of stairs on the right, abit after you take right at the fork towards the summit, those lead to the summit. Its a quick climb if you want to get to the summit quick, but it can be quite a challenge for some.

name: Bukit Timah Nature Reserve
review_text: Excellent place for hiking, with reinforced steps and boardwalks where needed to protect the soil and tree roots. There are numerous shaded forested trails and paths with varying levels of challenges in terms of slopes. Thoroughly enjoyed my workout!

name: Bukit Timah Nature Reserve
review_text:
Highest summit in Singapore.
Good and easy nature hike with lots of tree canopy cover. Not much sun even at 10.30am. Very doable with preschoolers.
We brought our own water bottles and we could conveniently refill them at the toilets at the bottom of the hill.

name: Bukit Timah Nature Reserve
review_text: Nice place for exercise n view scenery

name: Bukit Timah Nature Reserve
review_text: Great place. Totally doesn't have the city feel. Places like this in Singapore are not much. For those who like trekking, this could already be the best spot in SG. Also, walking areas are covered well with trees, so even in a sunny day, no need to worry about direct sunlight to your head.

name: Bukit Timah Nature Reserve
review_text: Nice little climb up to get your lungs working and heart pumping!

name: Bukit Timah Nature Reserve
review_text: Hidden Gem of singapore. It is very natural and well preserved, the hill is quite steep.

name: Bukit Timah Nature Reserve
review_text: Mangosteen tree at the visitor center is fruiting now.

name: Bukit Timah Nature Reserve
review_text: The best place to experience nature in Singapore. Lots of walking and running trails.  Wear a good pair of walking shoes, Tshirt, shorts, cap, carry some water and a light snack, and you are good to go.

name: Bukit Timah Nature Reserve
review_text:
Just like Sakura flower broom but not that big
And good look but colours is same...

name: Bukit Timah Nature Reserve
review_text: Lots of walkways. And it's better to go on the late mornings and early evenings to avoid a crowded car park. Difficult to find parking during the peak timings. And the trees canopy provides very good shady coverage. Hence, I don't really need to apply sunblock. Lots of tree shades almost throughout the walks there.

name: Bukit Timah Nature Reserve
review_text: Great facilities with different trails for varying levels of fitness. Hardcore hikers may be disappointed by the short height of the hill, that can't be helped. Visit just after heavy rain for best photo effects (mist) and cool air

name: Bukit Timah Nature Reserve
review_text: A fun thing to do when you want an activity to get your heart rate up a bit.  The hike to the top requires a person to climb a steep (very steep!) hill and about 10 flights of steep stone stairs.  It is not the most difficult thing that I have ever done but it is quite strenuous, especially in the heat of Singapore.

name: Bukit Timah Nature Reserve
review_text: I enjoy the trails here since they have varying elevations for a good workout.

name: Bukit Timah Nature Reserve
review_text: Varied good funs of tropical forest

name: Bukit Timah Nature Reserve
review_text:
My favourite hiking place when combine with the Dairy Farm loop - I used it for getting ready to climb Mt Agung, Mt Rinjani and the last one Mt Gede/Pangrango just before the pandemic.

It is also a good base to extend your distance with MacRitchie reservoir loop, Chestnut/Butterfly trail, Mandai T15 trail, the rail corridor to woodlands / tanjong pagar.

It is for everyone, take your own pace, once you get used to it, you can run down various trails or run up the summit push.

name: Bukit Timah Nature Reserve
review_text: A fantastic place to train for trekking expedition, relaxation walk, photo taking in this wilderness in Singapore.

name: Bukit Timah Nature Reserve
review_text:
A preserved natural beauty!  Kudos to authorities!

You can visit even in hot sun as the tall trees provides enough shade and you can feel the oxygenated air!  Joggers paradise!  Enjoy your time by sitting in chairs located beside the water body (rain water pool on rock quarry).

A place to spend time with family and friends of all ages.

name: Bukit Timah Nature Reserve
review_text: Nice short walk to the summit and a good place to spot colugos in the wild.

name: Bukit Timah Nature Reserve
review_text: Nice nature reserve for hiking and biking. Very crowded on the weekends. Followed Route 4 (yellow trail) which is not very long (I would guess 5kms) but can be challenging due to the number of stairs and steep incline in certain sections.

name: Bukit Timah Nature Reserve
review_text: Excellent Eco site with well maintained paths. Small carpark and large number of nature enthusiasts. So recommended to come early to beat the crowd but also for the cooler air!

name: Bukit Timah Nature Reserve
review_text: Bukit Timah Mountain Bike Trail is fantastic. 6.5km of twists and turns. Warning - not for a complete beginner and not for kids. Some of the drops are more than 2 feet. The uphill sections are at times tough and will require many to get off their bikes. Expect to get muddy - very muddy if its been raining. You can wash at a bike shop that is near the entrance to the trail head for 3 SGD.

name: Bukit Timah Nature Reserve
review_text:
This is a great place to spend your lazy day and get to sweat out by hiking the trails.  My personal favorite is the dairy farm loop, which includes a moderate share of uphill and downhill through the uneven steps.

Steps might be too steep for small children.

name: Bukit Timah Nature Reserve
review_text: This is perfect spot to eat post-hike. It‚Äôs one of the best hawker centers I‚Äôve seen with such a wide variety of choices; there‚Äôs even a bakery! Vegetarian thunder tea rice is very well-portioned and tastes great, but be prepared to stand in line.

name: Bukit Timah Nature Reserve
review_text:
Quite a steep hike, but like a little piece of the jungle in Singapore. You can see all kinds of wildlife here, especially monkeys.
If you are the sporty type and wish to head on the highest point (163.63M) in Singapore , please do come here! I would definitely go again.

name: Bukit Timah Nature Reserve
review_text: A Great place to hike and spend time with your friends and family. A must visit place located in the heart of Singapore that displays the beauty of Nature. A great place to go on a hike. They even have a vending cafe at the visiting centre. Well managed.

name: Bukit Timah Nature Reserve
review_text: So nice to have a green lung in the middle of Singapore. Proper rainforest with really well maintained paths. At the entrance there is a short trail with lots of different play areas for the kids. All in all, a wonderful place!

name: Bukit Timah Nature Reserve
review_text: If you enjoy hiking,  then you must visit Bukit Timah while in Singapore.

name: Bukit Timah Nature Reserve
review_text:
Is a good experience to enjoy the adventure of the place and have active hiking exercise or u can choose the paths walks and not so many stairs to climb up. You can heard the birds, squirrel, monkeys and so forth in some of the places.

There is toilet, vending machine near car park B. Do bring extra clothes, towel and insect repellent. Only open on weekend.

From car park A, u can take Blue Line (DT3) Hillview instead of going back to the main gate.

name: Bukit Timah Nature Reserve
review_text: A great hiking place for young and old. We went with a 7yo and a 71yo! There are different trails for different level of fitness. The trails are well kept and clean. We had a fantastic family bonding time with nature!

name: Bukit Timah Nature Reserve
review_text: Singapore hidden nature west side of central catchment.

name: Bukit Timah Nature Reserve
review_text: Nicely maintained pathways, dont recommend to go after 5pm because no lighted paths and lots of wildlife around. Be careful of construction areas and muddy areas so wear appropriate shoes for trekking.

name: Bukit Timah Nature Reserve
review_text: Great place for a hike with different routes for people of different fitness level. Just need to conquer the steep slope at the very beginning. Do go earlier if you drive as its harder to get a carpark lot if you reach about 8ish on weekends.

name: Bukit Timah Nature Reserve
review_text:
An amazing place to look around for nature! There are many bird species to look for, not to mention some butterflies, other cool creatures, and if you get there in January or winter you should be able some of the most cool migratory birds coming down from China and even Rusia.
Get there early since there are lot of people hiking and touring

name: Bukit Timah Nature Reserve
review_text: Whoa, who knew this mountain bike trail existed? It's pretty technical, and I imagine if I bike it several more times I'll get at least mildly injured -and yet it's so lush and beautiful and worth coming back to. Had a popped tire fiasco, so do bring a spare and small pump. Great ride, though

name: Bukit Timah Nature Reserve
review_text: Naturelovers will find it a quiet pice of Singapore. Enjoy nature while hiking to the summit and back down. There is a parking lot near the bottom. As for the walk, the path is well maintained. Be aware it is steep, so be sure to give yourself plenty of time to rest as necessary and bring a bottle of cold water.

name: Bukit Timah Nature Reserve
review_text: What a wonderful experience, a park well maintained! Peaceful and precious gem among the Singaporean parks!

name: Bukit Timah Nature Reserve
review_text: Jungle path starting from Diary Farm carpark is great for weight losing training.

name: Bukit Timah Nature Reserve
review_text: Starts off with a steep gradient slope initially. Then plateaus off for an easier stretch before the final climb up a 200m ladder of steep steps that will test your quads! The summit is pleasant and cool in the shade. The hubris surrounding this hill is well deserved.

name: Bukit Timah Nature Reserve
review_text:
While as a park itself it is a short one with some flora and fauna, crowds are very common here this leading to plenty of litter and noise affecting the tranquility you expect of nature.

The nearby quarry on the other hand does not seem to attract similar crowds but is certain and underrated beauty.

name: Bukit Timah Nature Reserve
review_text:
Nice place to see nature, with lots of bio-diversity.
Ideal for a walk, jog or cycling.

name: Bukit Timah Nature Reserve
review_text: NParks has done a brilliant job building and maintaining the reserve trails around the hill. Whether it's a short trek or a long looping escape through the jungle, there's something suitable for every fitness level. My wife and I have even used Bukit Timah as a regular training venue when we were preparing for our Kilimanjaro trek 2 years ago. I love this park. It's one of our little island nation's jewels. Please keep to the trails and help pick up any trash you see when you visit!

name: Bukit Timah Nature Reserve
review_text: Nice place for morning stroll. I don't work out regularly so I did not take the stairs to reach summit.. the main path is not difficult. The starting slope is tiring but it's worth trying. :)

name: Bukit Timah Nature Reserve
review_text: Very good tracking activity for entire family.  Different type of path for different levels of challenge. Fresh air and great view when you eventually reach the ridge line. Fellow trackers are friendly as well. Saw bikers there as well. Apparently there is a bike route too.

name: Bukit Timah Nature Reserve
review_text: Great place to hike and training for marathons,the path might be a little slippery and rocky but you just have to watch out for them. It us close to a bus stop so it is easy to reach there.

name: Bukit Timah Nature Reserve
review_text: One of the my favorite nature reserves in Singapore. I generally tend to take an early morning stroll during the weekends. It's so refreshing and one can enjoy the beauty of natural surroundings. If one is lucky, might even spot some wild animals. There are a number of pathways and  one can choose depending on the difficulty they want to endure.

name: Bukit Timah Nature Reserve
review_text: A beautiful place to go on a quick treck.

name: Bukit Timah Nature Reserve
review_text:
Nice place to visit for tracking and hiking. If you are nature lover it‚Äôs amazing place with different types of trees, flowers, insects and such a wonderful greenery...

We enjoyed a lot went in a group of around 20. Lot of beautiful places for photography.

name: Bukit Timah Nature Reserve
review_text:
Serene beauty, you can hike anytime even noon you don't feel hot over here

Especially the Singapore quarry has a splendid view which must not miss over there

Overall it was a nice experience, you can choose different types of paths from easy to difficult.

name: Bukit Timah Nature Reserve
review_text: My 1st visit after many years in Singapore (was born here üò∂). Great place to escape from the hustle of city life. Quite cooling even during hot day. Offers different trails and so suitable for young kids too. üòä

name: Bukit Timah Nature Reserve
review_text: For nature lovers. Feel free to visit any time of the day - the amount of trees here means you're almost always sheltered from the sun. I would not recommend any time after 4pm though, the mosquitoes should start popping out around sunset. Water coolers are available from both the Bukit Timah and Dairy Farm entrances, so just bring a bottle and remember to fill up before you start your hike. Oh, avoid carrying anything in plastic bags, or the monkeys will think you're Willy Wonka. Carry a backpack instead.

name: Bukit Timah Nature Reserve
review_text:
this is a perfect place here in singapore for outdoor enthusiast. You can do hiking ang mountain biking here.. the place is covered by trees.. it is also a good place to go if you want to exercise or do training climbs due to its steep trails and stairs going to its peak.
For those who do mountain biking, the trails is not recommended for beginners.

name: Bukit Timah Nature Reserve
review_text: Nice walking track with various route available. Did one and will go again. Well it is only good for trekking , don't expect any amazing mountain scenery

name: Bukit Timah Nature Reserve
review_text: Go off the beaten track and head towards Chestnut Park and relive the journeys of the original naturalists in Singapore 200 years back

name: Bukit Timah Nature Reserve
review_text: There is nothing really at the top, just a shelter and a boulder inscribed with the co-ordinates and height information.  However, the trails/tracks leading there are interesting because of the floral and fauna.  The difficulty levels of the trails cater to individuals with different abilities, from easy to difficult.

name: Bukit Timah Nature Reserve
review_text: The Nature Reserve is great for a weekend trek. There are various difficulty levels and the longest should be about half a day or so. Bring your own water bottle and snacks if you need. Visit all the viewpoints as some of them are a treat for those of us who are used to the city skyline.

name: Bukit Timah Nature Reserve
review_text: Around 1-2hours walk (subject to walking pace). The slope was pretty steep and required more effort climbing as compared to other nature reserves but nonetheless a great sense of satisfaction when reaching the top :)

name: Bukit Timah Nature Reserve
review_text: Amazing greenery in the middle of a bit city. Good place for running if you have hill climbs to do. It is good to bring a cap. If you are a bird watcher then bring a binocular as well.

name: Bukit Timah Nature Reserve
review_text: One of the last bastions of nature in Singapore that is still easily accessible to the public. Choose either the main road up or the trails, its an easy hike but dress for hot humid weather. Hiking boots not essential.

name: Bukit Timah Nature Reserve
review_text: Rainy Sunday with a lot of waterfalls(25.09.2022)

name: Bukit Timah Nature Reserve
review_text:
Great place for sending exercise. There are trails you can follow to get to MacRitchie Reservoir Park (11km walk).

Along the way you should see some wild life, at least the monkeys and monitor lizards.

This is one of the few nature parks that we still have,  and it is conveniently located.

name: Bukit Timah Nature Reserve
review_text: My go-to place if I need some Shinrin Yuku time. Good mix of easy to medium difficulty off-road trails such the Cave path, Jungle Falls path and the Dairy Farm loop. Good place to train for harder hikes like Mt K.

name: Bukit Timah Nature Reserve
review_text: Fantastic hiking location. Just be careful because the hill can be quite steep in places

name: Bukit Timah Nature Reserve
review_text: A beautiful and peaceful place to visit, definitely worth it for a visit and walk. There are many animals to see around and interesting trails to follow. Accessible to all kind of people and with routes with different hiking levels.

name: Bukit Timah Nature Reserve
review_text: Singapore highest hill at 163.63m. Reaching visitor centre at the foot of the hill by car and there's parking lots available.  Runners/ trekkers loves to do it via macrithie reservoir and going along rifle range road before reaching Bukit timah nature totally about 12-13km. Be prepared that OR will be packed with people during weekends, seeing highest number of visitors at about 9-11am. The first 200m or so of climb is very steep (a good hiking or running shoes with good traction will come in handy especially if it is raining) after which the slope gets a bit gradual.. Half way up the summit, you can choose to do it via the main route or do it via stairs. As it a nature park please be aware of snakes especially the blue coral snakes which is extremely venomous. There's vending machine and toilets sigh water coolers at the visitor centre. Gentle reminder, please do not feed the monkeys and do not leaves any rubbish behind. Remember LEAVE NOTHING BEHIND AND TAKE NOTHING AWAY!  When u are around nature. üòä

name: Bukit Timah Nature Reserve
review_text: Nice place for simple hiking

name: Bukit Timah Nature Reserve
review_text: The perfect venue to get some slope training done, clock some mileage, and get Ur dose of nature and fresh air! All in one small challenging but manageable package. I went during weekends, tends to get crowded by 7.30am.

name: Bukit Timah Nature Reserve
review_text: This place is great for hiking. The trail up to the highest peak wasn't very challenging for me as the distance was ok for me and the road was rather even. There is also a very clean toilet at the foot of the hill. Should visit if you haven't.

name: Bukit Timah Nature Reserve
review_text: If you want quick break from city life, go here. Nice forest with cool atmosphere.

name: Bukit Timah Nature Reserve
review_text:
These Natural reserves are to explore the Singaporean forests, if luck's with you, you may spot lizards, scorpions and some other wild creatures. You are sure to find small monkeys, squirrels and small bugs with plethora of trees of different varieties.
The entire walk to this reserve takes approx 1 hour, with a Normal pace.

name: Bukit Timah Nature Reserve
review_text:
A good place to walk. Stay on the tracks.
By the main track, just need 30-40 mins to reach the top.
Most strenuous would be the dairy farm track.
Migrant birds can be heard and spotted.
Have seen the Malayan Colugo a few times.

Quiet a safe place, as a jogger or hiker will usually come by.
But washroom is only available at the foot, at the visitor center (or at dairy farm area)

Bring water. No water at the hill top.

Not many mozzies (to me), so no need repellents, these  are not nature/creature friendly.

name: Bukit Timah Nature Reserve
review_text: This being very few nature reserves in Singapore there are many visitors. Its clean and green but quite noisy. I wished that people enjoyed being close to nature and talked less and talked softly. There are many chatty groups who disturb the peace and quite of the place. Bukit Timah has two paths to go up one via steps and the other is a road. I took the steps both times I went there,  it was a good test for the body both going up and coming down. Better to carry water bottle with you. And some energy bars it's a short distance but one or two hours can be easily spent there.

name: Bukit Timah Nature Reserve
review_text: Tranquility & good work out.

name: Bukit Timah Nature Reserve
review_text: Hiking in the rain. Nice experience.

name: Bukit Timah Nature Reserve
review_text: Great walking track! Good for a work out! Lovely escape from the city but the steps can be steep and might not be suitable for some people

name: Bukit Timah Nature Reserve
review_text: Great place to run n cycle

name: Bukit Timah Nature Reserve
review_text: Good sweat out spot for those finding a break from high rise buildings and likely a nature lover. If your a frequent hiker then you would be able to make fun of ameteurs. üòÅ

name: Bukit Timah Nature Reserve
review_text: A good place to visit for everyone.

name: Bukit Timah Nature Reserve
review_text: Bring plenty of water (you can buy them also at the centre)! You can reach Bukit Timah by MRT and then the bus. The entrance is a road that doesn't look suitable for pedestrians but you can walk there. Very tiring but worthwhile. We went on a sunny day and absolutely loved the walk. I like nature and you can even spot the Makaak monkeys. The top was somewhat disappointing because we wanted a nice view of the valley but it was all overgrown.

name: Bukit Timah Nature Reserve
review_text: Well if u want to hike, that's pretty much the only place in Singapore. Can access here to dairy farm loop, Singapore quarry, trek all the way to Macritchie reservoir. For tourist who wanna see monkeys, sure. Here is the place. And plenty of monitor lizard and sometimes wild boar too.

name: Bukit Timah Nature Reserve
review_text: Super steep hill at the starting point! But amazing place for a natural habitat. Check it out! Get away from the city and enjoy the beautiful greenery. Toilets available too. Not too sure abt lockers and bathing facilities.

name: Bukit Timah Nature Reserve
review_text: A place where you feel as one with nature..sweat the worries away and appreciate God's gift at it's best

name: Bukit Timah Nature Reserve
review_text: A bit crowded. Guess that it is expected since we cannot go overseas. But the air is fresh! Initial climb is quite steep. Get a good trekking shoes.

name: Bukit Timah Nature Reserve
review_text: One of the few outdoor activities with some level of excitement in SGP. If you are not concerned about a bit of exercise this is a nice climb in a jungle type of environment. You will be done within two hrs. For bikers there is an MTB trail with some challenges.

name: Bukit Timah Nature Reserve
review_text:
The best place so far for people looking for natural environment in Singapore. It has the highest point in Singapore that are practically reachable by walking on asphalt. It also has quarries that gives me chilling vibe.

In case you just want to jog, it has several flat route around the areas.

name: Bukit Timah Nature Reserve
review_text: The highest place in Singapore with primary forest surrounding it. However do not expect a view of Singapore at the peak. There are many trails. The dairy farm loop with its step stairs being the most challenging IMHO. Take the main road from the visitor centre to test those legs of yours. Half a day should be sufficient.

name: Bukit Timah Nature Reserve
review_text: Visited today for a short hike after it reopened lately. It was pretty crowded as it was a Sunday. It's convenient and easy to reach via the Downtown line. From Beauty World station, it's 10-15mins walk tot the visitor centre. The hike to the peak is similar to prior renovations, via a concrete slope in the beginning. From there, we continued towards Dairy Farm area, which was a pleasant route, not so crowded. Saw some monkeys along this route too!

name: Bukit Timah Nature Reserve
review_text:
A splash of nature in Singapore, with manmade paths and railings for easy exploration. There are a few entry points to the hill, so if you're going in a group be sure to specify which "entrance" to meet at!

The hill starts off pretty steep, but the gradient tapers off after a while. Perspiration is usually due to humidity and not exhaustion. It takes around 20 minutes to get to the summit, so don't expect a long hike!

name: Bukit Timah Nature Reserve
review_text: Very enjoyable walk. Quite a climb up slope. Very nice scenery. However advised to bring mosquito repellent  during mornings n evenings.

name: Bukit Timah Nature Reserve
review_text: Located off Hindhede Dr, it is popular with morning joggers and bird watchers. The main entrance is through the visitor centre at bottom of hill. Visitors will go up the steep path leading to the summit. Those looking for wildlife in the area will be disappointed, few were observed, a few butterfly habitats were located near the BKE animal bridge. More likely to see humans then wildlife. The place is not lit at night, the terrain is rough and trekking can be tough. Visiting at night is not recommended. A few paths in the area. The rock path, only for the fit and adventurous. The cave path, to find 2 closed caves. The catchment path, to lead to the butterfly habitats, the summit path leading to the summit. The dairy farm loop is full of steps and difficult to trek.

name: Bukit Timah Nature Reserve
review_text: Have never cease to love this place since i first step foot on it 4 decades ago. Have visited many times in my earlier years for birdwatching and of course military training. Now after almost a decade of absence it is such refreshing to see the forest and familsr sights again. But much has changed as some of the trails aee now off limit.

name: Bukit Timah Nature Reserve
review_text:
It's free, and they open from 7am to 7pm, the place is very well maintain, very clean, I saw a volunteer uncle picking up rubbish as he was trekking the path, an inspiration and good example to all.

If you're looking to train and polish your trekking and hiking skills, this would be a great place without the need to travel into Malaysia.

If you come from the main entrance, you will be greeted with a steep tarmac road which is very similar to Mt. Pulai in Johor. Right towards the summit, you can off trek into the Dairy Farm Loop, a well path nature walk but challenging as there is a ridiculous amount of steps going up and down, very good thigh and calve exercise, carry a heavy bag to simulate an actual hiking exercise.

name: Bukit Timah Nature Reserve
review_text: A pleasant place to take a walk alone üòä

name: Bukit Timah Nature Reserve
review_text: The new Dairy Farm Trail is 1.5hrs of stair climbing that is great for training. Lush tropical fauna and wildlife such as monitor lizards, squirrels and spotted a bat asleep in a tree. A great place to get away from urbanity.

name: Bukit Timah Nature Reserve
review_text: The main entrance is close to the Beauty World MRT station, 10 minutes walk to be specific, you get to walk on a inclined road and stairs inside to get to the top of the hill, best to go there in a group of 4 to 6 people together, enjoy half of your day covering around 10 to 12 kilometre on foot.

name: Bukit Timah Nature Reserve
review_text: Beautiful nature reserve for weekend trail walking, running or nature exploration. The reserve is connected to other places making it easy to navigate and not have to return to the same place. No refreshment points so bring plenty of water

name: Bukit Timah Nature Reserve
review_text: Went there for mountain biking on a Sunday morning. Don't worry hikers. There'll be a place for you to hike and a place for the bikers to ride. Nice to see alot of visitors. Good way to spend ur day away from work and move to nature.

name: Bukit Timah Nature Reserve
review_text: Beautiful place for trekking if you can escape from the crowd and noise. It is so busy during weekends with big groups blocking the paths and chatting loudly. Recommended to visit on weekdays.

name: Bukit Timah Nature Reserve
review_text: Beautiful nature reserve  to hike. A good location to learn about nature as the trees and flowers are labelled. Good place to exercise and relax during the weekend. There's also a path for mountain bike cyclist to go on an adventure ride through different terrains and courses.  A visitor center for all to understand about the history of Bukit  Timah Nature Reserve otherwise called as BT. Alot of wild birds, insects and some monkeys can be seen at this site.  All in all and enjoyable site if your want to exercise or even take a stroll there.

name: Bukit Timah Nature Reserve
review_text: Beautiful place for those who love Hiking!

name: Bukit Timah Nature Reserve
review_text:
This popular nature reserve is usually packed on a public holiday. Pay attention to the parking should you choose to park by the roadside leading to the nature reserve. Pick a spot with no double yellow line. A bold white line separating the lanes means you cannot park by the side. LTA passes by three times a day per a local resident.

There are 4 routes. 2 easy. Up and down wil be about 2.5 km. Kids friendly trail for route 1 and 2. Have fun.

name: Bukit Timah Nature Reserve
review_text: Good hike under the heat. Unfortunately not much to see. Little animals, no sight views... Only go there is you want to exercise: and beware of the trail with steep stairs!

name: Bukit Timah Nature Reserve
review_text: Kids had lots of fun fighting gravity while being protected from the sun under the canopy.

name: Bukit Timah Nature Reserve
review_text: A great deal of nature! You can spot snakes, monitor lizards and monkeys on your trail! Remember not to bring food along though as the monkeys might take the chance to snatch it away from you! They can become a little bit aggressive especially when it comes to food.

name: Bukit Timah Nature Reserve
review_text: Nature is amazing, few uphills. we were lucky to see lots of monkeys in this reserve than other reserves, is a bit quiet there  but you can still hear the traffic in the background while walking .

name: Bukit Timah Nature Reserve
review_text: Definitely a must visit in Singapore if you want to sweat out and test your stamina. Carry water bottles, spare t shirt, small towel. The trees on both sides of the road serve as a perfect shade from the sun. You can travel between 7 am- 7 pm. Might get humid initially. Even though if it‚Äôs a sunny day, you won‚Äôt feel the sun. Get down at Beauty World MRT on downtown line and walk about 500 m. It‚Äôs free!

name: Bukit Timah Nature Reserve
review_text: Car park still under renovation,  but otherwise this is a short but decent cardiovascular workout - about 20 minutes to reach the top. Really steep incline though. Make sure your shoes have adequate traction.

name: Bukit Timah Nature Reserve
review_text:
Go conquer the highest peak in SG :p

Don't forget to:
- bird watch
- trail the old railway
- hug a tree

name: Bukit Timah Nature Reserve
review_text: One of the best nature reserves in Singapore! Expect a lot of leg work as there are lots of stairs and slopes going both up and downhill. Bring insect repellent as mozzies are aplenty. Bring a raincoat too in case of wet weather as the shelters can be quite far apart.

name: Bukit Timah Nature Reserve
review_text: Handicap accessible parking. Lush greenery. The first 1/3 of the hike up is extremely steep but the rest of the trek up is much more gentle and pleasant hike. Warning. Lots of mosquitoes.

name: Bukit Timah Nature Reserve
review_text: Well covered by the trees from the sun. Lots of huts to shelter from the rain. View from the top was somewhat underwhelming though (big trees, which are lovely, somewhat spoil the view from this high point). Monitor lizards aplenty in the leaf litter. Toilets near to the visitor centre were clean. Drinking water also available there.

name: Bukit Timah Nature Reserve
review_text: Nice & great place for training Hiking

name: Bukit Timah Nature Reserve
review_text: Highest hill in Singapore. The nature paths around the summit are a great place to run. Might be a bit humid. Only thing is a lack of shower facilities at the visitor center. Unless one wants to shower using the foot taps

name: Bukit Timah Nature Reserve
review_text: Highest place in singapore. Good place to trek , run and biking .

name: Bukit Timah Nature Reserve
review_text: the trail was not bad. but there are some parts have changed since the last time that i‚Äôve been there when i was younger that time.and went to chestnut there for cycling and the trial at chestnut is like so called much easier then bukit timah trail as the bukit timah trial is like a good work out for the mountain cyclist like me with my transition mountain bike that i had for a few years already.

name: Bukit Timah Nature Reserve
review_text: Nice place to brisk walk. Easy to access and direction is displayed around the area so that individual able to take cautious if there is crocodile around the area or any wild animal visit the placed.

name: Bukit Timah Nature Reserve
review_text: Always a great spot for a good dose of fresh air and exercise. Beauty world MRT is within walking distance, various buses stop nearby, though public car parks (@hindhede or hillview) are a tad small n it's usually full if you come during 'peak' hrs (ie between 0600-0900, or 1600-1800hrs), just need to wait awhile though.

name: Bukit Timah Nature Reserve
review_text: Nice plan to just hike

name: Bukit Timah Nature Reserve
review_text: Untouched forest in a bustling city. Love the tall trees!

name: Bukit Timah Nature Reserve
review_text: A place for refresh your mind, train your body, and go mingle by doing sport with everyone

name: Bukit Timah Nature Reserve
review_text: Beautiful scenery, great walk with friendly patrons.

name: Bukit Timah Nature Reserve
review_text:
Be sure to wear proper footwear when entering. Makes the difference between a positive experience or not.
Signs and maps are placed at strategic spots so you won't be lost even if you didn't map out a path beforehand. Don't bring a plastic bag due to monkeys & beware of mosquitoes.

name: Bukit Timah Nature Reserve
review_text: One of my favorite places in Singapore. This is in the center of the Central Catchment Reserve (which includes MacRitchie Nature Park and the reservoirs). There are a lot of trails here for hiking and also some tough trails for serious mountain bikers. It can get a bit crowded during the weekends as this is a favourite exercise destination for locals. I have trekked all the trails in here and also managed to catch some awesome wildlife photos. Unfortunately, the "Rock Trail" has been closed due to erosion (since I got to Singapore last year, and up until this writing).

name: Bukit Timah Nature Reserve
review_text: Great place for hiking in SG. Not recommended for hiking alone. Suggest to take the Dairy Farm loop, which would take approx 1.5 hours to complete. Bring along snacks and drinking water. Beware of monkey snatching ur food.

name: Bukit Timah Nature Reserve
review_text: As a person who loves hiking and mountain biking, this is a nice place to go to as the trails are really nice and fun to ride as well as the hike up and exploring bukit timah but it is tiring but overall it is very enjoyable

name: Bukit Timah Nature Reserve
review_text: Nature. Good number of trails for the adventurous to get away from the urban once in a while. Be sure to bring ample water to stay hydrated, water coolers are available at some toilets. Keep food out of sight of the monkeys!

name: Bukit Timah Nature Reserve
review_text: The first 10 minutes are pretty steep but once you get past that, the rest of the hike is quite enjoyable!

name: Bukit Timah Nature Reserve
review_text: A sizeable patch of primary rainforest in the middle of one of the most densely populated cities in the World (so they say) . . . and they have monkeys there too! A lovely spot to reconnect with nature - lots of walking trails some of which link to other patches of wilderness that collectively make up The Central Catchment area and lungs of Singapore. Gorgeous

name: Bukit Timah Nature Reserve
review_text: Small island, this is pretty much as good as it gets! Enjoyable trek, nothing too tiring or difficult. Multiple options for trekkers to chose a longer route or something shorter depending on the time they have. üëçüèº

name: Bukit Timah Nature Reserve
review_text: Lovely foliage. Great for a walk to catch up with my friends.

name: Bukit Timah Nature Reserve
review_text: Most people know about Bukit Timah Nature Reserve because it's bigger but this is a challenging little training ground for those who enjoy running or biking up slopes and stairs. It's pretty secluded and while I was there I didn't see anyone else (it could be the blistering heat).

name: Bukit Timah Nature Reserve
review_text: This nature reserve has one of the highest points in Singapore. If you like nature and travelling to Singapore. I would suggest get a sneak peek here as well! They have lot of trails and some of them are tough and steeply inclined. Weekends it is very crowded. It is a very green area unlike other parts on Singapore! If you are a fitness enthusiast,this can be a good change of environment to go and practice!

name: Bukit Timah Nature Reserve
review_text: Not for the weak-hearted! Good for cardiac exercise.

name: Bukit Timah Nature Reserve
review_text:
Tropical jungle surrounding but with well defined and well marked paths.
Perfect if you want to take a few hours away from the noise to soak up some fresh air and get your heart pumping.

name: Bukit Timah Nature Reserve
review_text: Recently revamped boardwalk makes it much safer for families to explore off the tarmac road up the hill. Great place to get some exercise, although parking is extremely challenging on the weekends / public holidays.

name: Bukit Timah Nature Reserve
review_text: Nice place to walk and enjoy nature

name: Bukit Timah Nature Reserve
review_text: I rate Bt Timah Hill Nature Reserve no. 1 place for a good hike, for its very shady & refreshing greenery, peaceful & scenic environment. Initial climb up the hill is steep & will be quite challenging for those who have not exercised.

name: Bukit Timah Nature Reserve
review_text: We recently took the direct paved path up to the summit with a 4yr old and 8yr old, it only took approx 30mins. The initial steepness of the hill was daunting for them but we turned it into a fun game to search and look for insects and other animals in the surroundings. The time flew by.

name: Bukit Timah Nature Reserve
review_text: Work them leg muscles and get in touch with mother nature. Just the right amount amount of steps, slopes, pathway and amenities. Reach the top and earn bragging rights for reaching the 'Highest' point in Singapore.

name: Bukit Timah Nature Reserve
review_text: Hmmm‚Ä¶ not an expert in hiking but this park/reserve is kinda dull. We‚Äôve tried multiple routes which are not challenging and the sceneries are mediocre.

name: Bukit Timah Nature Reserve
review_text:
A welcome escape from the urban city hustle and bustle. Dress cool with comfortable shoes. There are multiple paths with varied difficulties. These are marked with colored stakes. Red striped stakes indicate the hardest.
The view at the top is the final destination, but the journey up or down the slopes is what makes this place special.
Take the time to savor the sounds, smells and sights of this hill .
If you have more time, walk to the quarry and take in the cliffs that has been formed from history of granite quarry. They used to mine these via explosives back in the 1960s.

name: Bukit Timah Nature Reserve
review_text: Be prepared for steep slopes. Do hike with trekking pole if you need some extra support for your uphill journey. You could picnic at the top of the hill, and there is this iconic carved rock that you could take picture with at the top of the hill (trust me, you won't miss the sight of the rock). The entire journey up hill only took 15mins, therefore I choose to explore the dairy farm loop, which took me approximately 55mins. Do also head to the Hindhede Quarry, which is just a stone throw away from the entrance of Bukit Timah Hill, you could view the (imo) most scenic view at the look out point (and you may also encounter monitor lizards on your way to the lookout point). There are really still and well camouflaged with the mud path too.

name: Bukit Timah Nature Reserve
review_text: Beautiful tropic reserve. The place is maintained and controlled by the highest standards.

name: Bukit Timah Nature Reserve
review_text:
Very nice trails.
Not too far/hard for parents with young kids who are over 4 or 5.
Also a good place to see how people maintain natural environment which is so close to urban.

name: Bukit Timah Nature Reserve
review_text: Great place for morning walk. Neat and clean. The stagnant water a bit challenging because it helps breading mosquitos and not very secure. Tower is nice. Hv a walk in free time.

name: Bukit Timah Nature Reserve
review_text:
I bring my kids there every now and then.

I like the idea of allowing them to get close to nature and have them walk down that beaten track and climb up that steep hill. It builds confidence, persevere and let them overcome the fear of small insects and animals.

I'm looking forward to the re-opening of the rock path; the kids wants to try climbing it again.

name: Bukit Timah Nature Reserve
review_text: Hiked from macritchie reservoir to bk timah hill, lots of nature and stuff. 9km +++

name: Bukit Timah Nature Reserve
review_text:
Tired! üòÜ Posted this while on summit.

Free Water
Free Toilet

There is a Gantry Carpark near the hill entrance. Some wild life can be seen and a small "waterfall".

name: Bukit Timah Nature Reserve
review_text: Good place to explore with great facilities

name: Bukit Timah Nature Reserve
review_text: It‚Äôs a beautiful nature reserve in the middle of Singapore. It gives you a sense of what Singapore would‚Äôve been like before all the development. We went on a trail called Durian Trail, we saw monkeys and lizards on our walk. Definite must if you‚Äôre getting sick of shopping centres in Singapore.

name: Bukit Timah Nature Reserve
review_text: started my weekly rountine to hike BT hill. its amazing to see so many people of all ages enjoying their hikes. Parking will be full so try taking public transport there

name: Bukit Timah Nature Reserve
review_text:
The best out of 4 official mountainbike trails/parks in Singapore. It snakes around the base of Bukit Timah; Nparks should allow some trails to be built on the hill itself. During the rainy season, water just flows down the hill and pools in the trails. If trails were allowed to be built on the hill itself, this wouldn't happen.

Also, many hikers/walkers tresspass on the trail despite many signs telling them not to. Then glare at you as you ride by.

name: Bukit Timah Nature Reserve
review_text: Nice place for natural visit, if you like hiking and photo taking try visiting this place, you may like it. But do remember to spray lots of insects repellent or else enjoy letting mosquito bites.

name: Bukit Timah Nature Reserve
review_text: Beautiful place but a bit too crowded on the weekend

name: Bukit Timah Nature Reserve
review_text: Lovely place to burn some calories after having Singapore's delicious food

name: Bukit Timah Nature Reserve
review_text: Probably the best nature reserve in Singapore with parts of it being prime rain forest. Big change to see monkeys and other wildlife. Nice hiking and mtb trails.

name: Bukit Timah Nature Reserve
review_text: This is nature, this is home. A quick trail walk during my weekend afternoon for a boost of Seratonin. Wonderful place. My only regret was not knowing how to look out for wildlife and plant species.

name: Bukit Timah Nature Reserve
review_text: Its great for a family workout as there are mamy stops along the way to the summit. For those that want to seriously work out, the stairs and the slope at the start are great.

Quarry's a beautiful place for instagramming and showing off your OOTDs/Sportswear

name: Bukit Timah Nature Reserve
review_text: The initial climb to the summit is one of a kind in Singapore. Weekday visits are encouraged because finding a parking lot is mission impossible during weekends.

name: Bukit Timah Nature Reserve
review_text: Quite nice hike, good exercise.  Good info at visitor center, though all vending machines are not well stocked and not kept operating well.  Also, don't go for a good view, as there is none.

name: Bukit Timah Nature Reserve
review_text: Nice trail with lots of greenery doesn‚Äôt have the views that one gets at MacRitchie Reservoir or Palau Ubin but one can enjoy a short rain forest trail that has lots of different loops and options. Be sure to buy water at the kiosk downstairs because they don‚Äôt have any kiosks on the trail.

name: Bukit Timah Nature Reserve
review_text: Want to start your day with simple exercise like walking or you want to explore possibilities this is the place for you. Hikes, slopes, walking, jogging, cycling you have ample amount of scope here and greenery to sooth your eyes.

name: Bukit Timah Nature Reserve
review_text: Good workout if you include the dairy farm route as well, but need to redo certain treks to clock a longer distance or training for a climb. Best nature reserve in Singapore.

name: Bukit Timah Nature Reserve
review_text: After being to many hiking and trekking spots around Singapore, this is one of the most enjoyable, with steep slopes that test your endurance and strength, and it adds a bit of challenge to complete all the trails in one session.

name: Bukit Timah Nature Reserve
review_text: I was expecting to see wild animals and lots of nice views. Unfortunately, I saw none of that. If you are looking for a hike, this is a great place to be challenged thanks to its steep terrain. Just don't expect nice views or spotting wild animals.

name: Bukit Timah Nature Reserve
review_text: There is a paved route straight to the summit and a network of trails that branch off from that route. A mountain biking trail also encircles the hill. Dairy Farm Quarry to the rear of the hill is definitely worth a visit if you have a couple of hours to spare. Alternatively, drive straight to the carpark at the rear of the reserve and walk five minutes to the Quarry.

name: Bukit Timah Nature Reserve
review_text: Pleasant forest walk. Drinking fountains are available at the start so you can refill your bottle. Some steep sections but worth it. Squirrels and monkeys are common.

name: Bukit Timah Nature Reserve
review_text: Small rain forest kinda park. Also some wild monkeys. Bring enough water with you. To get to the park by subway, use the 'beauty world' stop on the blue line. There you'll pass a shopping mall, so you can buy your water when forgotten as well as musquito spray. Then walk to the park

name: Bukit Timah Nature Reserve
review_text: One of the largest and oldest nature reserves in Singapore, also boasting the highest hill in Singapore. This is a place if you want to be one with nature. Wanting more excitement! There's a mountain biking trail which will put your physical prowess to the test!

name: Bukit Timah Nature Reserve
review_text: Lots of greenery. Fresh air and tough terrains for those looking for challenges. If you have keen eyes you could spot a Viper, a Oriental whip snake or a Colugo

name: Bukit Timah Nature Reserve
review_text: Great bit of nature, saw some cool lizards and butterflies. Easy to be alone and have some time to reflect and passing hikers give a friendly smile - just don't expect any views though

name: Bukit Timah Nature Reserve
review_text: If you can handle the heat it's a great walk.  Changed a lot over the years.  Lay out and trails much improved since my last visit. Well worth the visit

name: Bukit Timah Nature Reserve
review_text: Great nature preserve and a good place to go to get away from it all. Saw a fair amount of wildlife (monkeys, birds, lizards), and a good hike to get the blood flowing.

name: Bukit Timah Nature Reserve
review_text: Nature lovers, bukit timah is waiting for you üòä

name: Bukit Timah Nature Reserve
review_text: I trek regularly at Bukit timah nature reserve. From hindhede park headquarters all the way up to the summit. Takes about 30minutes to reach the submit. Occasionally, some wildlife such as cobras, pythons and blue corals can be spotted . Squirrels and monkeys are more common here . The air here is very fresh especially early in the morning . This place can be crowded on weekends.

name: Bukit Timah Nature Reserve
review_text: Love the serenity in the surrounding quarry. Has a sharp cliff in the start and about 120 stair steps before reach the summit.  Several route close for renovation expected until end 2016

name: Bukit Timah Nature Reserve
review_text: May be only 164 meters high but this park will get you huffing and puffing on the off-trails. Take on the side trails to have a quick escape from the city and enjoy the musky smell of rainforest.

name: Bukit Timah Nature Reserve
review_text:
My heart yearns for the gentle shades of its trees, the scent of the tropical rainforests, the sounds of its fauna and the soothing effect it offers for my tired soul. A definite must to those who loves or just want to experience Singapore's nature.

Be in one with nature, right before here in Singapore.

name: Bukit Timah Nature Reserve
review_text: Some places easy to access..some very difficult to access...

name: Bukit Timah Nature Reserve
review_text:
Bukit TImah Nature Reserve is probably the oldest nature reserve in Singapore. Originally slated for quarrying activities, it has since been conserved to become one of the few natural sanctuary in our garden city.

On the weekends, you can witness families taking a stroll up the famous "steep incline" that would make you regret the moment you take your first step - however, you will definitely feel like it's a good workout when you reach the very top.

The summit is the highest natural point in Singapore at over 200m, giving you an unobstructed view of the western part of Singapore.

The untouched forest houses a wide range of natural wildlife including birds, wild boars, and the pesky monkeys. Do note that it is an offence to feed them and the forest has an adequate supply of food for them.

There are also mountain bikers who take a specially constructed path that is filled with sharp turns on undulating terrain. Be careful not the trek along this path in the event you get hit by a bike.

If you read up more on the history of this location, you would come to realise that during World War II, this was the location that was fiercely defended by the Island Defence Force - staffed by inexperienced locals.

From Bukit TImah Nature Reserve, you can trek to the Dairy Farm, Rifle Range Road, and all the way to Macritchie Resevior if you so wish. Know that the memories you create here would be yours forever since it's a protected area as well.

name: Bukit Timah Nature Reserve
review_text: Quite a good workout but too crowded being being a public holiday. Nothing much to look at. No place to park and all the cars parked along the side with solid white line got a fine.

name: Bukit Timah Nature Reserve
review_text: Nice place for hiking

name: Bukit Timah Nature Reserve
review_text: The only natural mount in Singapore. Back to nature. It going to be real hot and wet. Do bring along a extra pair of clothing and towel. Bring water 2. Morning is the best time to visit when it a bit cooler and you want some bit of  nature. Lots of ppl so u normally will  not feel alone for too long.

name: Bukit Timah Nature Reserve
review_text: Good workout and clean trails. A lot of educational information available at different spots! Be prepared and plan your route before heading out to hike!

name: Bukit Timah Nature Reserve
review_text: Nice place for nature lovers‚ù§üòç‚ù§üòç‚ù§

name: Bukit Timah Nature Reserve
review_text: Lovely place to catch the bird songs here and do a bit of exercise. Spotted a visitor turning on her music loudly on her smartphone. It should be discouraged as we would like to listen to the forest' s natural noises of birds singing or crickets creaking.

name: Bukit Timah Nature Reserve

We also saw a flying lemur with a baby which I have never come across in Singapore. Plus Bukit Timah Hill is the highest natural point in Singapore at 163.63m.

name: Bukit Timah Nature Reserve

name: Bukit Timah Nature Reserve
review_text:
More suitable for nature lovers,joggers and fitness enthusiasts..

name: Bukit Timah Nature Reserve
review_text:
Wished I was 30 years younger, and I would be able to scale up and down much easier. Interesting struggle, some had altitude problem...

name: Bukit Timah Nature Reserve
review_text:
The Bukit Timah Nature Reserve is a small 1.64 square kilometre (400 acre) nature reserve near the geographic centre of the city-state of Singapore, located on the slopes of Bukit Timah Hill, Singapore's highest hill standing at a height of 163.63 metres, and parts of the surrounding area. The nature reserve is about 12 kilometres from the Downtown Core, Singapore's central business district.

Despite its small size, it is considered one of the most productive pieces of nature. Alfred Russel Wallace also thought highly of the place. Together with the neighbouring Central Catchment Nature Reserve, it houses over 840 species of flowering plants and over 500 species of fauna. Today, it is one of the largest patches of primary rainforest left in Singapore. The forest reserve was formally declared as an ASEAN Heritage Park on 18 October 2011
